<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title><%= appData ? appData.appName : "Health Tracker" %> - About</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>About <%= appData ? appData.appName : "Health Tracker" %></h1>

    <p>
      This is a small health and fitness tracking application built as part of the
      Dynamic Web Applications final lab.
    </p>

    <p>
      It stores users and workouts in a MySQL database, and exposes JSON APIs for
      programmatic access, as well as HTML pages for listing, adding and searching workouts.
    </p>

    <p>
      Features include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>MySQL database for users and workouts</li>
      <li>REST-style JSON endpoints for /users and /workouts</li>
      <li>EJS views for a simple web front end</li>
      <li>Password hashing using bcrypt for users</li>
      <li>Basic validation and sanitisation for form input</li>
    </ul>

    <p><a href="/">Back to home</a></p>
  </body>
</html>
